From {{prefix|en|a-|t1=not|pos1=''the [[alpha privative]]''|biogenesis|t2=principle that living organisms are produced only from other living organisms}}, from {{der|en|grc|α-||''the alpha privative, indicating the lack of something''}} + {{m|grc|βῐ́ος||life}} (ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*gʷeyh₃-||to live}}) + {{m|grc|γένεσις||origin, source; manner of birth; creation}} (ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ǵénh₁tis||birth; production}}). The words {{m|en|biogenesis}} and ''abiogenesis'' were both coined by English biologist {{w|Thomas Henry Huxley}} (1825–1895) in 1870 (see the quotation).<ref>Compare {{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

